Dogma of Ulutiu: No person is the superior of another, with the exception of Ulutius clerics, who are his representatives in this world and who are set in positions of leadership to pass on his wisdom to his people. Because animals share the same emotions, thoughts, and mortals as people (but express them differently) they should be respected on pain of Ulutius wrath. The villagers of the Great Glacier also believe that magic from any source is blasphemous and those that practice it should be shunned and driven away.

Welcome to the blessed town of Chillwyck!

All here dwell by the grace of the Frost Dawn, the Ice Maiden, Lady Cold, Blessed Goddess Auril to whom all pay homage!

Rules:
- Those who do not look kindly upon the Frost Maiden may not enter.
- Fire or heat are not permitted to be brought within these gates.
- Sheathe or do away with all weapons.
- Remove all face coverings.
- No summons are allowed, save with approval of the Church of Auril or White Guard.
- No familiars or companions taller then 8 foot are allowed, save with approval of the Church of Auril or White Guard.
- You shall commit no violence of any kind within town.
- The disruptive or aggressive use of magic is not allowed.
- You shall take nothing what is not yours.
- You shall not disturb the people of Chillwyck.
- The word of the Church of Auril and her White Guard shall be obeyed.

Not following these rules may result in fines, flogging or execution depending upon the nature of the violation and the word of the guardians and keepers of Chillwyck.

Hail Auril!
Welcome to the blessed town of Chillwyck!
